	url = {https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105017215999?origin=resultslist},
	abstract = {Festival and event planning has improved participant experiences and accelerated sustainable development thanks to tourism technology and artificial intelligence (AI). Due to the 4.0 digital revolution, AI is transforming hospitality operations, demand forecasting, and customer pleasure. Virtual and augmented reality provide interactive tutorials and improve user experience. Mobile apps offer instant booking and updates. Tourism, sustainable development, and economic growth benefit from AI. This chapter examines how AI and technological innovation affect Europe's sustainable development goals (SDGs), focusing on green solutions to lessen the industry's environmental impact and raise awareness. However, labor shrinkage, skill gaps, ethics, cybersecurity, and economic implications exist. Festivals improve economic growth and social welfare by promoting cultural exchange and community. Events and tourism organizations satisfy client needs through social media and chatbot communication and customization. The chapter covers AI's economic, social, and environmental downsides. It reviews research on hotels, event planners, and music festivals using technology and AI to encourage sustainable growth in Europe. A mixed-method study examines how European tourism has leveraged technology and AI for sustainable growth. AI helps festivals and events attract and engage participants, boosting operations, customer experiences, and sustainability. Tourism sustainability, customer satisfaction, and process efficiency are improved by AI. Addressing privacy, employment displacement, and ethics is essential to responsibly deploy AI. AI concerns privacy and data security issues, automation-related job losses, and ethical challenges about justice and trust. Tourism businesses must fund research and development (R&D), work with technology providers, and involve stakeholders to integrate AI. Society must also advocate AI use responsibly. Companies should prioritize AI-based personalization, data protection, retraining, ethical AI, and stakeholder involvement. Future research should address AI's economic and social effects. © CAB International 2025. All rights reserved.},
