	abstract = {In the course of the ages, technology has played a crucial role in shaping events and festivals. Innovations such as the printing press and the digital realm have greatly improved communication, the business, and overall experiences. The evolution of technology has had a noteworthy impression on events and festivals over time. Initially, events were limited to local areas and relied on word of mouth. The emergence of the computerized services in the later years of the 20 th century transfigured event promotion and ticket sales. Mobile applications redefined onsite experiences by offering timetables, maps, and real-time notifications. In general, technology has facilitated the connection, promotion, and improvement of the whole process of events and festivals, making them more accessible and captivating for a wide range of people. This research study examines the changing influence of technology on the organization, implementation, and enjoyment of events and festivals across time. The research offers a detailed historical viewpoint on the interconnected relationship between technology and community celebrations, spanning from ancient rites to contemporary mega-events. © CAB International 2025. All rights reserved.},
